{"by":"taeric","id":47779664,"parent":47773812,"text":"This is as useless as the circular view that releasing dependencies for others to test makes you a free-rider on them using your stuff.<p>Which, honestly, I think it is fair to say that a lot of supply chains are lulling people into a false sense of what they do.  Your supply chain for groceries puts a lot of effort into making itself safe.  Your supply chain for software dependencies is run more like a playground.","time":1776263945,"type":"comment"}